I"/<p>Ever wondered if the reviews mentioned on Amazon, Flipkart are fake ? You are not alone as product companies too build algorithms to weed them out regularly. We have listed 8 key signs which can identify a fake review. These should help you save some time and money !</p>

<p>Reviews could very much fake if they -</p>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>Have very less, fake or even no profile information (like only nick names, no purchase history)</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Have only opinions that are all-or-nothing in nature</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Multiple similar ones that are posted at the same time/day</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Don’t go into detail about the item concerned</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Are very short (e.g., “This is really good.”)</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Have extensive use of small, simpler and more commonly used words (e.g., ‘big’, ‘bad’, ‘good’)</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Have no personal data of the reviewer (no photo)</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Are by a reviewer who has reviewed only a particular seller or product</p>
  </li>
</ol>

<p>Want to help in building a more comprehensive list ? Please share in the comments section below</p>

